349
00:26:20,665 --> 00:26:23,751
No. What I chose was a man I
could love for more than a week.

350
00:26:28,965 --> 00:26:31,509
I shouldn't have said that. I...

351
00:26:31,510 --> 00:26:34,429
At least you're being honest.

352
00:26:34,430 --> 00:26:38,475
I can't live moment to
moment like you, Adam.

353
00:26:38,476 --> 00:26:42,437
I have a history with Francis,
I have a future with him,

354
00:26:42,438 --> 00:26:45,231
and it's bigger than a moment.

355
00:26:46,441 --> 00:26:48,401
Then you should kill it...

356
00:26:48,402 --> 00:26:51,653
whatever part of you still loves me.

357
00:26:53,655 --> 00:26:56,618
If you can't,

358
00:26:56,619 --> 00:26:58,660
I will.

359
00:27:01,663 --> 00:27:04,125
- Adam...
- No.

360
00:27:30,944 --> 00:27:35,114
- Hello?
- Hey. Hey, sweetie.

361
00:27:36,533 --> 00:27:39,369
How's it going? I'm...
are you with your mom?

362
00:27:39,370 --> 00:27:42,288
She's downstairs. You
want me to go get her?

363
00:27:42,289 --> 00:27:45,583
No. No. I just wanted to call

364
00:27:45,584 --> 00:27:48,252
and say, uh,

365
00:27:48,253 --> 00:27:51,381
you know, hey to your...
uh, your brother and you.

366
00:27:51,382 --> 00:27:52,965
Is he... is he there?

367
00:27:52,966 --> 00:27:56,219
He's in his room, I think.

368
00:27:56,220 --> 00:27:58,513
Okay. You wanna go get him?

369
00:27:58,514 --> 00:28:00,056
Hold on.

370
00:28:12,360 --> 00:28:15,530
He says he doesn't want to talk to you.

371
00:28:15,531 --> 00:28:18,824
Wh... why not?

372
00:28:18,825 --> 00:28:21,244
We've seen the news, dad.

373
00:28:21,245 --> 00:28:25,289
There were all sorts of TV
cameras at our school yesterday.

374
00:28:25,290 --> 00:28:28,459
Mom's making us stay home this week.

375
00:28:33,881 --> 00:28:37,218
I want you to do something.
I want you to go to, uh,

376
00:28:37,219 --> 00:28:40,471
your bedroom window and look out.

377
00:28:42,181 --> 00:28:44,350
You see that black car?

378
00:28:44,351 --> 00:28:47,144
- Yeah.
- That's me.

379
00:28:47,145 --> 00:28:51,190
You shouldn't be here, dad.
Mom would be really angry.

380
00:28:51,191 --> 00:28:54,611
Well, we don't need to tell her.

381
00:28:54,612 --> 00:28:56,195
Right?

382
00:28:56,196 --> 00:28:58,948
It'll just be... it'll just be, uh...

383
00:28:58,949 --> 00:29:01,534
it'll just be our little secret.

384
00:29:01,535 --> 00:29:03,578
Your voice sounds weird,

385
00:29:03,579 --> 00:29:05,996
like it did on the radio.

386
00:29:08,750 --> 00:29:10,710
You... you heard that?

387
00:29:10,711 --> 00:29:13,045
I have a computer.

388
00:29:13,046 --> 00:29:15,548
Uh, 

389
00:29:15,549 --> 00:29:18,551
I'm sorry.

390
00:29:18,552 --> 00:29:20,511
I...

391
00:29:20,512 --> 00:29:23,389
Sometimes your dad makes mistakes.

392
00:29:23,390 --> 00:29:25,308
- I better go.
- No.

393
00:29:25,309 --> 00:29:28,102
I don't like to hear your
voice when it's like this.

394
00:29:28,103 --> 00:29:31,105
It makes me sad. Bye, dad.

395
00:29:31,106 --> 00:29:32,898
Sarah, please...

396
00:29:58,966 --> 00:30:01,093
Peter?

397
00:30:01,094 --> 00:30:02,679
Christina.

398
00:30:02,680 --> 00:30:04,263
Where are you?

399
00:30:04,264 --> 00:30:06,223
I'm, uh...

400
00:30:07,224 --> 00:30:09,935
Mm. I'm not...

401
00:30:09,936 --> 00:30:12,062
I'm not... I'm not doing so well.

402
00:30:12,063 --> 00:30:14,190
Where are you, Peter?

403
00:30:16,942 --> 00:30:20,571
- I'm in my car.
- Are you driving?

404
00:30:20,572 --> 00:30:21,781
No.

405
00:30:21,782 --> 00:30:24,492
Tell me where you are.

406
00:30:24,493 --> 00:30:26,786
I'm outside my kids' house.

407
00:30:26,787 --> 00:30:29,121
- You mean Madeleine's?
- Yeah.

408
00:30:29,122 --> 00:30:31,081
I need you to stay right there.

409
00:30:31,082 --> 00:30:32,958
Okay, Peter?

410
00:30:32,959 --> 00:30:35,169
You'll stay there?

411
00:30:36,546 --> 00:30:38,506
Peter.

412
00:30:38,507 --> 00:30:41,008
Peter, are you still there?

413
00:30:41,009 --> 00:30:42,968
Hello?

414
00:30:43,886 --> 00:30:45,388
Hello?

415
00:31:15,459 --> 00:31:17,503
I'd like to turn myself in.

416
00:31:17,504 --> 00:31:19,589
For what?

417
00:31:20,757 --> 00:31:23,175
A few months ago,

418
00:31:23,176 --> 00:31:26,512
I was pulled over for drunk driving.

419
00:31:26,513 --> 00:31:28,681
They let me go. I should've been convicted.

420
00:31:28,682 --> 00:31:33,185
Well, if you were let go, sir,
we can't arrest you for it now.

421
00:31:36,397 --> 00:31:40,150
Well, I drunk drove
here. Arrest me for that.

422
00:31:41,235 --> 00:31:43,654
We can put you in a detox tank...

423
00:31:43,655 --> 00:31:46,407
I wanna be formally arrested.

424
00:31:46,408 --> 00:31:49,744
My name is congressman Peter Russo.

425
00:31:51,203 --> 00:31:55,165
I was arrested in January
on Michigan Avenue.

426
00:31:58,294 --> 00:32:00,546
Please have a seat, Congressman.

427
00:32:04,675 --> 00:32:06,969
I gotta make a few phone calls.

428
00:33:08,781 --> 00:33:11,659
- Have you found him?
- I'm in front of his ex-wife's house.

429
00:33:11,660 --> 00:33:13,160
But Christina said he called from there.

430
00:33:13,161 --> 00:33:16,121
- He's not there?
- No.

431
00:33:16,122 --> 00:33:18,958
But his phone is. I found it by the curb.

432
00:33:18,959 --> 00:33:20,459
So we have no way to contact him?

433
00:33:20,460 --> 00:33:22,962
Not unless he reaches out to us.

434
00:33:22,963 --> 00:33:24,421
This isn't good.

435
00:33:24,422 --> 00:33:26,089
Want me to alert the authorities?

436
00:33:26,090 --> 00:33:29,010
Let's give him a little longer.

437
00:33:29,011 --> 00:33:32,137
- How long did it last?
- About six months.

438
00:33:32,138 --> 00:33:35,182
- He was older.
- A lot?

439
00:33:36,893 --> 00:33:38,435
Yeah.

440
00:33:38,436 --> 00:33:42,272
Was he a journalist, or
did he work on the hill?

441
00:33:44,107 --> 00:33:47,236
I'd rather not say.

442
00:33:47,237 --> 00:33:49,321
All right.

443
00:33:52,157 --> 00:33:55,160
He was someone I looked
up to... for a while.

444
00:33:56,954 --> 00:33:58,998
Why did it end?

445
00:34:00,541 --> 00:34:02,501
He has a wife.

446
00:34:02,502 --> 00:34:06,463
We both knew it was gonna end eventually.

447
00:34:06,464 --> 00:34:10,009
I mean, it was really...

448
00:34:10,010 --> 00:34:12,887
it was fucked up.

449
00:34:12,888 --> 00:34:14,889
The first night we spent together,

450
00:34:14,890 --> 00:34:17,224
he told me he was gonna
hurt me and then discard me.

451
00:34:17,225 --> 00:34:18,935
And when it ended,

452
00:34:18,936 --> 00:34:21,562
I told him that he'd done neither.

453
00:34:21,563 --> 00:34:25,357
But... it does hurt.

454
00:34:25,358 --> 00:34:27,568
I won't hurt you.

455
00:34:27,569 --> 00:34:30,279
Yeah, you can't promise me that.

456
00:34:30,280 --> 00:34:32,281
Yes, I can.

457
00:34:36,326 --> 00:34:39,455
- Has anyone else seen him?
- No.

458
00:34:39,456 --> 00:34:42,875
He's in an interrogation room by himself.

459
00:34:44,501 --> 00:34:48,255
I never should've got mixed
up with this fucking mess.

460
00:34:48,256 --> 00:34:50,883
We're way behind regret time, Barney.

461
00:34:52,259 --> 00:34:54,971
Just have your guys keep him out of sight.

462
00:34:54,972 --> 00:34:57,180
I'll need a back exit.

463
00:35:22,873 --> 00:35:24,959
- I got him. Thanks.
- Yeah.

464
00:35:24,960 --> 00:35:26,418
Come on.

465
00:35:36,929 --> 00:35:40,099
Hey, Peter.

466
00:35:40,100 --> 00:35:42,225
Where's your car?

467
00:35:45,104 --> 00:35:47,106
It's down the street.

468
00:35:47,107 --> 00:35:50,651
I'll drive you home. You go back
to mine, have Meechum let you in.

469
00:35:50,652 --> 00:35:52,945
- This way?
- Yeah.

470
00:35:57,908 --> 00:36:01,453
What were you thinking, Peter?

471
00:36:01,454 --> 00:36:04,665
I need to take
responsibility for my actions.

472
00:36:04,666 --> 00:36:06,709
By getting yourself thrown in jail?

473
00:36:06,710 --> 00:36:09,712
Real responsibility.

474
00:36:09,713 --> 00:36:12,673
Like... like they talk
about in the meetings,

475
00:36:12,674 --> 00:36:14,967
not the lies we told for the campaign.

476
00:36:14,968 --> 00:36:17,011
What you just did was extremely reckless.

477
00:36:17,012 --> 00:36:19,138
I don't care.

478
00:36:21,765 --> 00:36:24,894
I'm making a statement tomorrow, Frank.

479
00:36:26,562 --> 00:36:28,856
- About pulling out of the race?
- Mm-mm.

480
00:36:28,857 --> 00:36:32,442
That's not enough. I...

481
00:36:33,903 --> 00:36:36,405
I need to stop hiding.

482
00:36:39,992 --> 00:36:42,036
Well, let's work together on the language.

483
00:36:42,037 --> 00:36:44,872
I have to do it on my own.
It's gotta be my own words.

484
00:36:44,873 --> 00:36:47,624
Look, Peter, this isn't just
about you anymore, all right?

485
00:36:47,625 --> 00:36:50,794
- Let me help you.
- I don't want your help.

486
00:36:53,255 --> 00:36:57,009
I didn't never ask your help
when you... I got arrested.

487
00:36:57,010 --> 00:36:59,053
When did your help ever help me?

488
00:37:01,346 --> 00:37:03,432
You can live your life the way you want to.

489
00:37:03,433 --> 00:37:06,185
I'm done being told how to live mine.

490
00:37:08,771 --> 00:37:11,774
Well, there has to be a
way to take responsibility

491
00:37:11,775 --> 00:37:15,444
without shattering everything.

492
00:37:18,155 --> 00:37:21,242
Are you at least willing
to have that discussion?

493
00:37:47,810 --> 00:37:51,105
- Do you want me to come upstairs?
- No.

494
00:38:12,501 --> 00:38:15,921
I know you're in a lot of pain, Peter.

495
00:38:18,215 --> 00:38:21,135
But I don't want you to
feel any pain tonight.

496
00:38:21,136 --> 00:38:23,720
Here. You can start fresh tomorrow.

497
00:38:23,721 --> 00:38:27,474
Go ahead. I won't judge you.
Hell, I'll even join you.

498
00:38:32,271 --> 00:38:34,356
Just relax.

499
00:38:35,816 --> 00:38:37,901
You're home now.

500
00:38:44,408 --> 00:38:46,493
Whatever it is you have to face tomorrow,

501
00:38:46,494 --> 00:38:48,954
you don't have to face it now.

502
00:38:50,706 --> 00:38:53,542
Right now it's just you and me.

503
00:38:57,420 --> 00:39:00,257
The rest of the world doesn't matter.

504
00:39:02,634 --> 00:39:05,512
Your children, Christina...

505
00:39:05,513 --> 00:39:07,639
they will forgive you,

506
00:39:07,640 --> 00:39:10,600
because you're loved, Peter.

507
00:39:11,935 --> 00:39:13,979
Failed.

508
00:39:16,982 --> 00:39:19,109
I failed myself.

509
00:39:19,110 --> 00:39:21,611
I failed my family.

510
00:39:22,905 --> 00:39:25,615
I failed the campaign.

511
00:39:27,910 --> 00:39:29,995
No, you haven't, Peter.

512
00:39:32,706 --> 00:39:34,791
May I?

513
00:39:50,599 --> 00:39:52,726
You know, when Claire
and I were first married,

514
00:39:52,727 --> 00:39:55,979
we talked about having children.

515
00:39:55,980 --> 00:39:59,066
I told her flat out I didn't want any.

516
00:39:59,067 --> 00:40:02,778
It was selfish but honest.

517
00:40:02,779 --> 00:40:05,655
I didn't have a
particularly happy childhood.

518
00:40:05,656 --> 00:40:07,866
I suspect you didn't either.

519
00:40:07,867 --> 00:40:09,201
No.

520
00:40:09,202 --> 00:40:11,870
You see, no person avoids pain.

521
00:40:11,871 --> 00:40:13,872
And I just didn't think it was right

522
00:40:13,873 --> 00:40:16,041
to bring a child in knowing that.

523
00:40:18,501 --> 00:40:22,214
But now when I think back, I...

524
00:40:22,215 --> 00:40:25,008
I realize that was cowardly.

525
00:40:27,928 --> 00:40:29,805
I see you,

526
00:40:29,806 --> 00:40:32,433
and I think, well, there's a brave man,

527
00:40:32,434 --> 00:40:34,517
far braver than me.

528
00:40:34,518 --> 00:40:37,396
I'm so tired.

529
00:40:39,148 --> 00:40:43,402
When I... when I think about... when I...

530
00:40:43,403 --> 00:40:46,113
I'm so tired.

531
00:40:49,825 --> 00:40:52,369
You should close your eyes.

532
00:40:55,538 --> 00:40:57,874
Let it all go.

533
00:41:01,211 --> 00:41:04,589
We have all the time in the world.

534
00:41:09,511 --> 00:41:11,263
Peter?

535
00:41:19,604 --> 00:41:21,690
Peter.

536
00:43:38,868 --> 00:43:40,912
I walked back.

537
00:43:56,094 --> 00:43:58,680
Whatever happens in the next few hours,

538
00:43:58,681 --> 00:44:00,932
whatever you hear,

539
00:44:02,476 --> 00:44:04,769
we will never speak of it.

540
00:44:39,762 --> 00:44:41,682
Sir...

541
00:44:43,684 --> 00:44:46,727
I heard from Linda
about a half an hour ago.

542
00:44:46,728 --> 00:44:48,813
The President wants to meet with you.

543
00:44:48,814 --> 00:44:50,649
8:30.

544
00:44:52,859 --> 00:44:55,111
About what?

545
00:44:55,112 --> 00:44:57,531
I don't know.

546
00:45:07,541 --> 00:45:09,501
Frank.

547
00:45:17,509 --> 00:45:20,387
Now, when you brought up
this idea, I wasn't sold.

548
00:45:20,388 --> 00:45:24,224
It struck me as both
desperate and careless.

549
00:45:24,225 --> 00:45:28,103
But then Linda laid out all the pros,

550
00:45:28,104 --> 00:45:30,855
and they clearly outweigh the cons.

551
00:45:30,856 --> 00:45:34,901
I explained our reasoning to Jim and hoped
he wouldn't think I was off my rocker.

552
00:45:34,902 --> 00:45:39,448
I did at first, but the President
made some very good arguments.

553
00:45:39,449 --> 00:45:41,824
It's a bold move, Frank.
I'm very impressed.

554
00:45:41,825 --> 00:45:44,369
Well, thank you, sir, for
being open to the idea.

555
00:45:44,370 --> 00:45:46,996
And thank you, Mr. President,
for taking the risk.

556
00:45:46,997 --> 00:45:48,998
We'll need to work this out step by step.

557
00:45:48,999 --> 00:45:51,543
- The execution has to be perfect.
- Where are things with Russo?

558
00:45:51,544 --> 00:45:53,712
- Any word from him yet?
- We're still trying to locate him.

559
00:45:53,713 --> 00:45:55,922
- Well, is there any cause for worry?
- It's been two days.

560
00:45:55,923 --> 00:45:58,216
I am a bit worried, I have to admit.

561
00:45:58,217 --> 00:46:00,427
I mean, this must be an extremely
difficult moment for him.

562
00:46:00,428 --> 00:46:02,220
We're hoping he'll reach out shortly.

563
00:46:02,221 --> 00:46:04,889
Let's get our people on it.
I wanna know where he is.

564
00:46:04,890 --> 00:46:06,975
Now, once he withdraws,
we have to move quickly.

565
00:46:06,976 --> 00:46:09,561
We'll make a joint
statement, as you proposed.

566
00:46:09,562 --> 00:46:11,563
It's a clear message, I think.

567
00:46:11,564 --> 00:46:14,232
Pennsylvanians matter to us, and
we're not gonna let them down.

568
00:46:14,233 --> 00:46:17,402
That's right. I'll say that Jim's an
invaluable asset to the White House,

569
00:46:17,403 --> 00:46:19,946
but that I have great
admiration for the sacrifice

570
00:46:19,947 --> 00:46:21,948
he's willing to make for
the people of his home state.

571
00:46:21,949 --> 00:46:24,534
And you should not accept his
resignation until he's elected.

572
00:46:24,535 --> 00:46:28,079
- That will show your continuing commitment to him.
- I think that's a good idea.

573
00:46:28,080 --> 00:46:30,499
As long as I can devote myself
wholly to the campaign, I agree.

574
00:46:30,500 --> 00:46:33,502
Now, should Jim win, we'll need to
nominate a Vice President immediately.

575
00:46:33,503 --> 00:46:35,545
Linda, you're putting
together a list of names?

576
00:46:35,546 --> 00:46:37,589
Yes. And you can begin the vetting process

577
00:46:37,590 --> 00:46:39,174
as soon as you narrow down the choices.

578
00:46:39,175 --> 00:46:41,301
I already have a short
list of top contenders.

579
00:46:41,302 --> 00:46:44,102
- I want your input on that, Jim.
- More than happy.

580
00:46:46,222 --> 00:46:48,141
Congressman?

581
00:46:50,268 --> 00:46:51,936
Congressman?

582
00:47:08,036 --> 00:47:09,746
We can use the existing infrastructure.

583
00:47:09,747 --> 00:47:11,623
Are you okay with Nash Aarons?

584
00:47:11,624 --> 00:47:14,459
I like Nash, but I'll want to
bring in some of my own people.

585
00:47:14,460 --> 00:47:16,628
Well, that won't be a
problem. Nash is a team player.

586
00:47:16,629 --> 00:47:19,880
And we can reallocate some of your
existing 2016 reelection funds...

587
00:47:19,881 --> 00:47:21,966
Excuse me. Linda.

588
00:47:22,883 --> 00:47:24,969
Peter Russo is dead.

589
00:47:26,012 --> 00:47:27,888
Suicide.

590
00:47:27,889 --> 00:47:31,142
He was found in his garage
with the car still running.

591
00:47:34,354 --> 00:47:36,857
I'm so sorry, Frank.

592
00:47:36,858 --> 00:47:40,569
- May I have a moment, sir?
- Of course.

593
00:47:40,570 --> 00:47:43,780
I will get more information
and start drafting a statement.

594
00:47:43,781 --> 00:47:46,907
Let's reschedule.
Whenever is best for Frank.

595
00:48:02,549 --> 00:48:05,677
Congressman Peter Russo was found dead

596
00:48:05,678 --> 00:48:08,137
early this morning in the parking garage...

597
00:48:08,138 --> 00:48:11,349
- why didn't we break this?
- ... Of his apartment building in Washington D.C.

598
00:48:11,350 --> 00:48:14,644
U.S. Secret Service Agents
discovered his body after reports

599
00:48:14,645 --> 00:48:17,480
- ... that Russo had been missing since Saturday.
- Fuck!

600
00:48:17,481 --> 00:48:20,817
His body was transferred
to the D.C. coroner's office

601
00:48:20,818 --> 00:48:25,321
where an autopsy is expected to
confirm his death as a suicide.

602
00:48:25,322 --> 00:48:27,783
A junior congressman from Philadelphia...

603
00:48:27,784 --> 00:48:29,701
- Zoe.
- ... Russo was 36 years old...

604
00:48:29,702 --> 00:48:32,370
- Look at this.
- ... And is survived by two children.

605
00:48:32,371 --> 00:48:36,291
- I gotta get to the office.
- Russo was in the midst of a heated battle

606
00:48:36,292 --> 00:48:38,460
for the governorship of Pennsylvania.

607
00:48:38,461 --> 00:48:41,755
He was last heard publicly during
a morning political radio show

608
00:48:41,756 --> 00:48:44,299
on Pittsburgh station WZPZ.

609
00:48:44,300 --> 00:48:47,636
Now, during the interview, he slurred
his words, he sounded disoriented...

610
00:48:47,637 --> 00:48:49,763
- Christina.
- ... Leading many to believe

611
00:48:49,764 --> 00:48:52,973
- ... that he had relapsed...
- Can you get me a train back to D.C.?

612
00:48:52,974 --> 00:48:54,810
Right here on this TV station

613
00:48:54,811 --> 00:48:56,603
for all your late-breaking details

614
00:48:56,604 --> 00:48:58,104
about this major news story:

615
00:48:58,105 --> 00:49:01,357
The suicide of congressman Peter Russo.

616
00:51:20,455 --> 00:51:24,793
I find it very difficult to express
everything that I'm feeling right now,

617
00:51:24,794 --> 00:51:27,796
and I know Claire feels exactly the same.

618
00:51:27,797 --> 00:51:30,715
Peter was very special to us.

619
00:51:30,716 --> 00:51:33,509
A sort of magnetic presence

620
00:51:33,510 --> 00:51:34,743
that electrified everyone he touched.

